The information you are seeking is related to the disclosure of teacher lists for undergraduate courses offered by USJT. According to Portaria Normativa MEC nº 23 de 2017 and Law nº 9.394/1996, the list of teachers who teach a course must be disclosed to students or interested parties.

The list of teachers must include the following information:

* Name of the teacher;
* Campus where the teacher is based;
* Course taught;
* Nominal grade;
* Date of last update.

The list of teachers must be disclosed in a specific page on the institution's website, and it must be updated semestraly or annually, depending on the duration of the courses offered. The list must include the following information:

* Data of the last update;
* Name of the course taught;
* Campus where the course is offered;
* Nominal grade;
* Date of last update.

The disclosure of the teacher list must be done until one month before the beginning of the courses, and it must be done in a specific page on the institution's website. The list must be updated semestraly or annually, depending on the duration of the courses offered.

In addition, the unities curricular disciplines of the undergraduate courses offered by USJT are judged tadeu, and they have a semestral duration, as it is stated in the pedagogical projects of the course. The list of teachers must be referencied as the list of active professors at the end of the second semester of 2022.

